channel.title: [PI] webclient error while loading?
channel.description:
Im trying to make a webclient and my client.jar wont load it says this - same as webclient
i jsut found something out!t! [size=18pt]this is before i jarred it[/size] - in my client there is a file called "raw" with it the client works and without it says the same error as the webclient...do i have to add this to the cache folder? i dont know at all what to do
Im trying to make a webclient and it looks like everything is loading perfect then while its loading it says
[sub]"Sorry, an error has occurred whilst loading cursedpkz. To fix this try the following(in order) 1.Close all browser windows and reloading - check, still not working 2.Try clearing cache - done, still not working 3.Try using different game world - I don't know if this even applies... 4.Try rebooting your computer - done, still broken 5.Try selecting a different version of Java from the play game menu"[/sub]
use this url to see what i mean - http://cursedpkz.webs.com/webclient.htm
umm i have no idea how to fix this can some please help me !!!!!!!!! i will pay some1 if they can give me a working solution for this error or who can fix it for me with teamviewer
THIS IS THE TUT I FOLOWED - http://www.google.org/runescape-development/rs2-client/tutorials/253018-how-make-your-project-insanity-client-webclient.html
this is my client!
http://www.mediafire.com/?gx8gh9do3v8t7qv if any1 could try make a webclient out of it and get it working i will happly pay them for the fix or working webclient from what i can afford please help

item.title: [PI] webclient error while loading?
item.dc:creator: @death_t_d death t d
item.description:
@death_t_d wrote:

i know how to fix man. Open ur client.java file and search for: ./raw
then change it to the location of ur cache example; c:/.urclientnamehere_cache/Raw
then u have to put the raw file in ur cache then re-zip it. then re-upload ur cache and change the download link in ur signlink.java to ur new download link and ur all set. Oh and dont forget to jar it after
